														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3626944">
									

<p>Liked the end and found the body thoroughly entertaining. The soul-slave thing ties up the whole affair in a nice horror bow - while that seems to be becoming the norm for MC&amp;D articles it didn't really detract from my overall appreciation of the whacky-ish tone that underscores the piece's darker moments. I'm not a particularly big fan of the execution; it seems almost cheat-y, taking this ridiculous concept (an app for anomalous people) and then having MC&amp;D treat it as a legitimate business premise, with regulations and precautionary measures, etc., but in the end that's sufficiently dampened by the fact you make a decent case for their sponsorship of it. The fact that it's really just a data-hoarding scheme suits their characterization as corporate bastards very nicely.</p>

							</div>

								
